{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/rainbow-text/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"itsopensource"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"873387f2-d03c-5842-b48d-1d84dc7bd14d","excerpt":"Some designers can not get enough of colors and want the text not to be in solid color but rainbow colors. Traditionally developers achieve this by using a PNGâ€¦","html":"<p>Some designers can not get enough of colors and want the text not to be in solid color but rainbow colors. Traditionally developers achieve this by using a PNG image, something like this:\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 450px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/246eb855d94926b75dc96c8d8b336e73/fc2a6/rainbow.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 33.108108108108105%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Rainbow Text\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/246eb855d94926b75dc96c8d8b336e73/fc2a6/rainbow.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/246eb855d94926b75dc96c8d8b336e73/12f09/rainbow.png 148w,\n/static/246eb855d94926b75dc96c8d8b336e73/e4a3f/rainbow.png 295w,\n/static/246eb855d94926b75dc96c8d8b336e73/fc2a6/rainbow.png 450w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>But with modern day CSS, this can be achieved with just few CSS rules.</p>\n<h3>How</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a Div</li>\n<li>Add some text</li>\n<li>Add some basic styling like <code class=\"language-text\">font-size</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">line-height</code> etc.</li>\n<li>Add a background color <code class=\"language-text\">background: linear-gradient(45deg, red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet, red);</code>: Rainbow ðŸŒˆ</li>\n<li>Add this property to the div <code class=\"language-text\">background-clip: text</code>: This makes sure the background is only used for the available text</li>\n<li>Add <code class=\"language-text\">color: transparent</code>: This makes sure that the clipped background on text is completely visible.</li>\n<li>Thatâ€™s it ðŸ˜Ž</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Code</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.rainbow-text</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n   <span class=\"token property\">background</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">linear-gradient</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>45deg<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> red<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> orange<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> yellow<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> green<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> blue<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> indigo<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> violet<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> red<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n   <span class=\"token property\">background-clip</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> text<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n   <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> transparent<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n   <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 40px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h4>DEMO</h4>\n<style>\n .rainbow-text {\n   background: linear-gradient(45deg, red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet, red);\n   background-clip: text;\n   color: transparent;\n   font-size: 60px;\n   font-weight: 900;\n   font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\n}  \n</style>\n<div class=\"rainbow-text\">Trishul Goel</div>\n<p>Right click and inspect the text above and observe the CSS in inspector.</p>\n<center>Hope this helps ðŸ˜Š </center>\n<br/>","frontmatter":{"title":"Rainbow text with CSS","tags":["css","design"],"date":"February 11, 2024","description":null,"author":"trishul","featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/rainbow-text/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-switch-namespace-in-kubernetes/"},"frontmatter":{"author":"shivam","tags":["devops","kubernetes","how-to"],"title":"How to Switch Namespaces in Kubernetes"}},"next":null}},"staticQueryHashes":["4268877247","764694655"],"slicesMap":{}}